{"name":"Guard","type":"background","img":"icons/equipment/shield/heater-wooden-blue.webp","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Ability Score Increases:</strong>&nbsp;+1 to Strength and one other ability score.</p><p><strong>Skill Proficiencies:&nbsp;</strong>Intimidation, and either Athletics or Investigation.</p><p><strong>Languages:</strong>&nbsp;One of your choice.</p><p><strong>Suggested Equipment (Cost 11 gold):</strong>&nbsp;Common clothes, halberd, uniform.</p><p><strong><em>Feature: Natural Authority</em></strong><strong>.&nbsp;</strong>Commoners and civilians sometimes assume you are part of a local constabulary force and defer to you.</p><p><strong><em>Adventures and Advancement</em></strong><strong>.&nbsp;</strong>When you visit the city or countryside you once patrolled you&rsquo;re sure to get embroiled in the same politics that drove you out. Should you stick around righting wrongs, you might accidentally find yourself in a position of responsibility.</p><h3><strong>GUARD CONNECTIONS</strong></h3><ol><li>The corrupt guard captain who framed you.</li><li>The by-the-book guard captain who found you in violation of a regulation.</li><li>The mighty guard captain who taught you all you know.</li><li>The informant who tipped you off about criminal activity.</li><li>The noble or merchant you protected.</li><li>The comrade or superior officer you admired.</li><li>The villain who kidnapped the person you were charged to protect.</li><li>Your betrayer, the one person you didn&rsquo;t think to mistrust.</li><li>The noble or merchant who had everyone in their pocket.</li><li>The diviner wizard who could usually provide you with the missing piece of a puzzle.</li></ol><hr><h3><strong>GUARD MEMENTOS</strong></h3><ol><li>Your badge of office, a symbol of an ideal few could live up to.</li><li>Your badge of office, a symbol of a corrupt system you could no longer stomach.</li><li>The arrow-damaged prayer book or playing card deck that saved your life.</li><li>The whiskey flask that stood you in good stead on many cold patrols.</li><li>Notes about a series of disappearances you would have liked to put a stop to.</li><li>A broken sword, torn insignia, or other symbol of your disgrace and banishment.</li><li>A tattoo or insignia marking you as part of an organization of which you are the last member.</li><li>The fellow guard&rsquo;s last words which you will never forget.</li><li>A letter you were asked to deliver.</li><li>A bloodstained duty roster.</li></ol>","schemaVersion":{"version":0.019,"lastMigration":{"version":{"schema":0.018,"foundry":"11.315","system":"0.18.11"}}},"grants":{"FKTWF5WHGR8R0XJ3":{"grantType":"ability","level":0,"optional":false,"_id":"FKTWF5WHGR8R0XJ3","default":true,"img":"","label":"Ability Score Increase","abilities":{"base":["str"],"options":["str","dex","con","int","wis","cha"],"total":1},"bonus":"1","context":{"types":["base"],"requiresProficiency":false}},"ewHg3v2fZ5kcYdfW":{"grantType":"item","level":0,"optional":true,"_id":"ewHg3v2fZ5kcYdfW","default":true,"img":"","label":"Suggested Equipment","items":{"base":[],"options":[{"uuid":"Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.w9t45o2j9aqx1qmp","quantityOverride":0},{"uuid":"Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.56f3xn2t5hv917jk","quantityOverride":0}],"total":1}},"Hsof8F5AMqW3vSRu":{"grantType":"trait","level":0,"optional":false,"_id":"Hsof8F5AMqW3vSRu","default":true,"img":"","label":"Languages","traits":{"base":[],"options":["abyssal","aquan","auran","celestial","common","deep","draconic","druidic","dwarvish","elvish","giant","gnoll","gnomish","goblin","grimlock","halfling","ignan","infernal","minotaur","mycelial","orc","primordial","sylvan","terran","cant","undercommon"],"total":1,"traitType":"languages"}},"d3MMja8syAYRedD6":{"grantType":"proficiency","level":0,"optional":false,"label":"Skill Proficiencies","keys":{"base":["itm"],"options":["ath","inv"],"total":1},"proficiencyType":"skill","_id":"d3MMja8syAYRedD6","default":true,"img":""},"vFfDe2HE1xZiepfE":{"grantType":"feature","level":0,"optional":false,"label":"Feature","features":{"base":[{"uuid":"Compendium.a5e.a5e-background-features.Item.dgl1bp93fxkjkawn","limitedReselection":true,"selectionLimit":1}],"options":[],"total":0}}},"source":"adventurersGuide"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"_id":"f3hw79b7wjo9huy4"}
{"name":"Gambler","type":"background","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/playing-cards.webp","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Ability Score Increases:</strong>&nbsp;+1 to Charisma and one other ability score.</p><p><strong>Skill Proficiencies:</strong>&nbsp;Deception, and either Insight or Sleight of Hand.</p><p><strong>Tool Proficiencies:&nbsp;</strong>Gaming set (dice set, playing cards set).</p><p><strong>Suggested Equipment (Cost 16 gold):</strong>&nbsp;Fine clothes, dice set, playing card set.</p><p><strong><em>Feature: Lady Luck.</em></strong>&nbsp;Each week you may attempt a &ldquo;lucky throw&rdquo; to support yourself by gambling. Roll a d6 to determine the lifestyle you can afford with your week&rsquo;s winnings (1&ndash;2: poor, 3&ndash;5: moderate, 6: rich).</p><p><strong><em>Adventures and Advancement.</em></strong>&nbsp;Once you&rsquo;ve had more than your fair share of lucky throws, you attract the attention of richer opponents. You add +1 to all your lucky throws. Additionally, you and your friends may be invited to exclusive games with more at stake than money.</p><h3><strong>GAMBLER CONNECTIONS</strong></h3><ol><li>The mentor you have now surpassed.</li><li>The duelist who will never forgive you for fleecing them.</li><li>The legendary gambler you aspire to beat.</li><li>The friendly rival who always keeps you on your toes.</li><li>The noble who publicly accused you of cheating.</li><li>An ink-stained academic who wants you to test a risky theory about how to beat the house.</li><li>The gang leader who would rather kill you than pay up.</li><li>The kid who strives to emulate you.</li><li>The cardsharp rival who cheats to win.</li><li>The rival who won something from you that you want back.</li></ol><hr><h3><strong>GAMBLER MEMENTOS</strong></h3><ol><li>Gambling debts owed you by someone who&rsquo;s gone missing.</li><li>Your lucky coin that you&rsquo;ve always won back after gambling it away.</li><li>The deeds to a monster-infested copper mine, a castle on another plane of existence, and several other valueless properties.</li><li>A pawn shop ticket for a valuable item&mdash;if you can gather enough money to redeem it.</li><li>The hard-to-sell heirloom that someone really wants back.</li><li>Loaded dice or marked cards. They grant advantage on gambling checks when used, but can be discovered when carefully examined by someone with the appropriate tool proficiency (dice or cards).</li><li>An invitation to an annual high-stakes game to which you can&rsquo;t even afford the ante.</li><li>A two-faced coin.</li><li>A torn half of a card&mdash;a long-lost relative is said to hold the other half.</li><li>An ugly trinket that its former owner claimed had hidden magical powers.</li></ol>","schemaVersion":{"version":0.019,"lastMigration":{"version":{"schema":0.018,"foundry":"11.315","system":"0.18.11"}}},"grants":{"EK23hsIgIRCYQiqm":{"grantType":"ability","level":0,"optional":false,"_id":"EK23hsIgIRCYQiqm","default":true,"img":"","label":"Ability Score Increase","abilities":{"base":["cha"],"options":["str","dex","con","int","wis","cha"],"total":1},"bonus":"1","context":{"types":["base"],"requiresProficiency":false}},"btIa5RiOYONUdZb9":{"grantType":"feature","level":0,"optional":false,"_id":"btIa5RiOYONUdZb9","default":true,"img":"","label":"Feature","features":{"base":[{"uuid":"Compendium.a5e.a5e-background-features.Item.lo5obt0px93qczpg","limitedReselection":true,"selectionLimit":1}],"options":[],"total":0}},"9T8EScAkLUWhbW3Q":{"grantType":"proficiency","level":0,"optional":false,"label":"Skill Proficiencies","keys":{"base":["dec"],"options":["ins","slt"],"total":1},"proficiencyType":"skill","_id":"9T8EScAkLUWhbW3Q","default":true,"img":""},"2mgdu7mE3QgUYvjC":{"grantType":"item","level":0,"optional":true,"label":"Suggested Equipment","items":{"options":[{"uuid":"Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.fs1g83t1y18hflen","quantityOverride":0},{"uuid":"Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.8immo7012y7uj9u7","quantityOverride":0},{"uuid":"Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.nzk5o2pu6bk18d67","quantityOverride":0}],"total":1,"base":[]},"_id":"2mgdu7mE3QgUYvjC","default":true,"img":""},"yXBWmFyk7Bo9r20m":{"grantType":"proficiency","level":0,"optional":false,"label":"Tool Proficiencies","traits":{"base":["diceSet","playingCardSet"],"options":[],"total":0,"traitType":"tools"},"keys":{"base":["diceSet","playingCardSet"],"options":[],"total":0},"proficiencyType":"tool"}},"source":"adventurersGuide"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"folder":null,"_id":"ozxxla8s8niqzw9w"}
{"name":"Folk Hero","type":"background","img":"icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp","system":{"description":"<p>You were born to a commoner family, but some event earned you fame. You&rsquo;re admired locally, and tales of your deeds have reached the far corners of the world.</p><p>Did you win your fame by battling an oppressive tyrant? Saving your village from a monster? Or by something more prosaic like winning a wrestling bout or a pie-eating contest?</p><hr><p><strong>Ability Score Increases:</strong>&nbsp;+1 to Constitution and one other ability score.</p><p><strong>Skill Proficiencies:&nbsp;</strong>Survival, and either Animal Handling or Nature.</p><p><strong>Tool Proficiencies:</strong>&nbsp;One type of artisan&rsquo;s tools, one vehicle.</p><p><strong>Suggested Equipment (Cost 2&ndash;31 gold):&nbsp;</strong>Any artisan&rsquo;s tools except alchemist&rsquo;s supplies, common clothes.</p><p><strong><em>Feature: Local Fame</em></strong><strong>.</strong>&nbsp;Unless you conceal your identity, you&rsquo;re universally recognized and admired near the site of your exploits. You and your companions are treated to a moderate lifestyle in any settlement within 100 miles of your Prestige Center.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><em>Adventures and Advancement</em></strong><strong>.&nbsp;</strong>Common folk come to you with all sorts of problems. If you fought an oppressive regime, they bring you tales of injustice. If you fought a monster, they seek you out with monster problems. If you solve many such predicaments, you become universally famous, gaining the benefits of your Local Fame feature in every settled land.</p><h3><strong>FOLK HERO CONNECTIONS</strong></h3><ol><li>The bard whose song made you legendary and who wants a sequel.</li><li>Your friend, a traveling merchant whose caravan spreads your fame.</li><li>A deadly enemy: the heir of the oppressive noble you killed.</li><li>A deadly enemy: the mother of the monster you killed.</li><li>A deadly enemy: the leader of the bandits you defeated.</li><li>A deadly enemy: the tyrant you robbed.</li><li>A kid who wants to follow your footsteps into danger.</li><li>The jealous rival who wants to best your monster-slaying prowess, daring deeds, prize pie recipe, or whatever else made your famous.</li><li>A secret admirer: the heir or heiress of the oppressive noble you defeated.</li><li>The retired adventurer who trained you and is now in a bit of trouble.</li></ol><hr><h3><strong>FOLK HERO MEMENTOS</strong></h3><ol><li>The mask you used to conceal your identity while fighting oppression (you are only recognized as a folk hero while wearing the mask).</li><li>A necklace bearing a horn, tooth, or claw from the monster you defeated.</li><li>A ring given to you by the dead relative whose death you avenged.</li><li>The weapon you wrestled from the leader of the raid on your village.</li><li>The trophy, wrestling belt, silver pie plate, or other prize marking you as the county champion.</li><li>The famous scar you earned in your struggle against your foe.</li><li>The signature weapon which provides you with your nickname.</li><li>The injury or physical difference by which your admirers and foes recognize you.</li><li>The signal whistle or instrument which you used to summon allies and spook enemies.</li><li>Copies of the ballads and poems written in your honor.</li></ol>","schemaVersion":{"version":0.019,"lastMigration":{"version":{"schema":0.018,"foundry":"11.315","system":"0.18.11"}}},"grants":{"Vv4dUQWOkDiaIjfX":{"grantType":"ability","level":0,"optional":false,"_id":"Vv4dUQWOkDiaIjfX","default":true,"img":"","label":"Default ASI","abilities":{"base":["con"],"options":["str","dex","con","int","wis","cha"],"total":1},"bonus":"1","context":{"types":["base"],"requiresProficiency":false}},"LMLeUe1CqhKS5oXX":{"grantType":"item","level":0,"optional":true,"_id":"LMLeUe1CqhKS5oXX","default":true,"img":"","label":"Suggested Equipment 1","items":{"base":[],"options":[{"uuid":"Compendium.a5e